Abstract:.  Isotopic series of neutron - deficient
secondary projectiles were produced by projectile
fragmentation using a 1 A GeV 238U beam.  Cross
sections of fission induced by nuclear and
electromagnetic interactions in a secondary lead target
were measured.  They were found to vary smoothly as a
function of proton and neutron number of the fissioning
system, also for nuclei with large ground-state shell
effects near the 126-neutron shell.  No stabilization
against fission was observed for these nuclei at low
excitation energies.  Consequences for the expectations
on the production cross sections of super-heavy nuclei
detectors was measured.  The detectors were used to
determine horizontal positions of the fragments at the
central and at the final focal plane.
Second detector served as a start detector to measure
